<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Settings - Phone Backup Portal</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container">
      <header class="topbar">
        <h1>Phone backup setup</h1>
        <form action="/api/auth/logout" method="post">
          <button class="button" type="submit">Log out</button>
        </form>
      </header>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>Step 1: Your upload link</h2>
        <p>
          Open this link on your phone to upload photos and videos to your
          account:
        </p>
        <div class="upload-link"><%= uploadUrl %></div>
        <% if (typeof uploadQrDataUrl !== "undefined" && uploadQrDataUrl) { %>
        <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Or scan this QR code:</p>
        <img
          src="<%= uploadQrDataUrl %>"
          alt="QR code for your upload link"
          style="max-width: 180px; background: #fff; padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.75rem;"
        />
        <% } %>
        <p class="muted">
          Make sure your friends only share their personal upload link with
          people they trust.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <h2>Step 2: Create folders & download</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          Folders are labels you use to group uploads. You choose one of your
          folders on the phone when uploading, then download everything for that
          folder on desktop.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a class="button" href="/folders">Manage folders & download all</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <h2>Your server storage usage</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          You can keep up to 2 GB of files on the server. When you are done
          with old uploads, delete them to free space before starting a large
          new transfer.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong><%= fileCount %></strong> file(s) using
          <strong><%= (totalBytes / (1024 * 1024)).toFixed(2) %> MB</strong> of
          <strong><%= (maxBytes / (1024 * 1024 * 1024)).toFixed(1) %> GB</strong>
          available.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
          To delete data from the server, go to your folders and remove files or
          whole folders before uploading more.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p>
        <a href="/batches">&larr; Back to your uploads</a>
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

